\v 14 Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign: Behold, the young woman will conceive and bear a son and will call his name Immanuel.\f + \ft Instead of \fqa the young woman\fqa* some ancient manuscripts have \fqa a young woman.\fqa*\f*
\v 15 He will eat curds and honey when he knows to refuse the evil and choose the good.
\v 16 For before the child knows to refuse the evil and choose the good, the land will be desolate, though you fear the faces of its two kings.
\v 17 Yahweh will bring the king of Assyria on you and on your people, and on the house of your father days that have not come since the day Ephraim turned away from Judah.”

