\q2 and fall and be broken and be ensnared and captured.

\m
\v 16 Bind up the testimony; seal the law for my disciples.
\v 17 And I shall wait for Yahweh, who hides his face from the house of Jacob, and I shall hope in him.
\v 18 Behold, I and the children whom Yahweh has given to me {are} for signs and for wonders in Israel from Yahweh of hosts, who lives on Mount Zion.

\p
\v 19 And when they say to you, “Consult with mediums and with soothsayers, the ones who chirp and mutter,” how can a people not consult with their God, but with the dead on behalf of the living?
\v 20 To the law and to the testimony! If they do not say as this thing, {it is} because they have no dawn,
\v 21 and will pass through it distressed and hungry. And it will happen when they are hungry, then they will become angry and curse their king and their God and turn upward.
\v 22 And they will look at the earth and behold: trouble and darkness, dimness, distress and gloom is scattered.


\c 9
\p
