\v 5 And they will be dismayed and ashamed, because of Cush, their hope, and of Egypt, their glory.
\v 6 And the inhabitants of these coasts will say on that day, ‘Behold, this {was} our hope, where we fled for help to be rescued from the face of the king of Assyria, but how can we escape?’”


